Cell.Text: Well, look at this. Another city rat crawled outside the walls. I don't suppose you've come up here to tell old Froki about your supposed Divines?
Just what we need. City folk barging in, probably looking for an offering to their precious Divines.
Good. This is Skyrim, and we should honor the old ways. These foreigners don't even respect their own gods, much less Kyne and her Sacred Trials.

Node.Caption: dunHunterAtheistBranchTopic: Not me. I don't believe in the Divines.

Cell.Text: [S] It's an old Nord Tradition, a test to prove your worth in the eyes of Kyne. Show that you're a hunter and no simple butcher. | Kyne teaches us to respect the beasts and blesses the hunter who will face their champions. True Nord hunters are those who survive the Trials.
Do you think you're strong enough for Kyne's blessing? I would be glad to pass this tradition down.
[S] You must defeat guardian beasts, blessed by Kyne.

Node.Caption: dunHunterAcceptQuest: Yes. Tell me what to do.

Cell.Text: [S] S|I'll anoint you with the symbol of the wolf, the crab and the skeever. This will compel the guardian to appear when you reach his lair.
Return when you've defeated the guardian wolf, crab and skeever.

Node.Caption: dunHunterTier01BranchTopic: What do I need to do?

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> Here's where you need to go.
Don't mock it, pup. Even the lowliest beasts can kill the weak and arrogant. We'll try more powerful enemies next, if you survive this.

Node.Caption: dunHunterQSTSkeeverWhat: A guardian skeever? Are you serious?

Cell.Text: G|That's what an old man gets for thinking the younger generation might be interested in learning some honor.
They're stolen idols! Imposter gods, sold by silver tongues. No thank you. Froki will not forget Kyne, or her Sacred Trials.

Those sycophants in the Temple would call her Kynareth. Just a pale shadow of the truth, like all the Temple Divines. | Kyne! Blessed Warrior-Wife. Shor's widow, sacred to any true Nord hunter. She's the mother of men and beasts, and her veil is the storm.
[S] Maybe you're not so soft, after all. Now you're ready for a real challenge. | I'll anoint you with the symbol of the Bear, the Sabrecat and the Mammoth. Tread carefully, these are mighty beasts.
What should I do now?
[S] The guardian spirits of Bear, Mammoth and Sabre Cat await you. Return when they are defeated.
What should I do now?
[S] Kyne's guardian troll awaits you. Complete this trial and you'll have proven yourself a true hunter.
[S] You do Kyne proud. Only one challenge remains. Go and defeat the troll champion.
I've defeated the guardian troll.
[S] Then you finally know what it means to be a true hunter, in the Nord way. | For this you have earned the Blessing of Kyne, and can count me as a friend.
S|I don't believe it. I made that bow myself. Been through some messes with it, let me tell you. | You know what? I want you to keep it. My great hunts are behind me, but yours are yet to come.

Node.Caption: dunHunterFrokiBowTopic: I found this bow. Is it yours?

Cell.Text: S|Grandson. He's a strong lad. His parents were at Helgen when, well you know.
Do you like having Haming around?
Can't say I was a great father the first time around. Now that he's here it's like a second chance. He's a good lad.
